Objectives / Learning Outcome(s) / Major:
•	DISTINGUISH BETWEEN DIRECT COSTS AND INDIRECT COSTS, VARIABLE COSTS AND FIXED COSTS, INVENTORIABLE COSTS FROM PERIOD COSTS.
•	CALCULATE STATIC BUDGETS AND STATIC-BUDGET VARIANCES, FLEXIBLE-BUDGET VARIANCES, SALES-VOLUME VARIANCES, PRICE VARIANCES, EFFICIENCY VARIANCES, VARIABLE OVERHEAD FLEXIBLE-BUDGET VARIANCE, THE VARIABLE OVERHEAD EFFICIENCY VARIANCE, AND THE VARIABLE OVERHEAD SPENDING VARIANCE, THE FIXED OVERHEAD FLEXIBLE-BUDGET VARIANCE, THE FIXED OVERHEAD SPENDING VARIANCE, AND THE FIXED OVERHEAD PRODUCTION-VOLUME VARIANCE.
•	CALCULATE THE COST OF PRODUCTS USING VARIOUS PRODUCT COSTING METHODS, SPECIFICALLY ABSORPTION, VARIABLE, AND THROUGHPUT COSTING METHODS;
•	DISTINGUISH BETWEEN RELEVANT AND IRRELEVANT INFORMATION AND MAKE SOUND BUSINESS DECISIONS USING MANAGERIAL ACCOUNTING INFORMATION;
•	USE INCREMENTAL ANALYSIS IN MAKING SHORT-TERM DECISIONS SUCH AS MAKE-OR-BUY AND SPECIAL ORDER DECISIONS. 
•	FORMULATE AND SOLVE LINEAR-PROGRAMMING PROBLEMS.
•	DISTINGUISH JOB COSTING FROM PROCESS COSTING, AND ACTUAL COSTING FROM NORMAL COSTING.
•	DISTINGUISH BETWEEN SIMPLE AND ACTIVITY-BASED COSTING SYSTEMS.
•	ACCOUNT FOR SPOILAGE, REWORK, AND SCRAP.
•	ALLOCATE SUPPORT DEPARTMENT COSTS USING DIRECT, STEP-DOWN, AND RECIPROCAL METHODS; COMMON COSTS USING THE STAND-ALONE AND THE INCREMENTAL METHODS; AND BUNDLED REVENUES TO THE INDIVIDUAL PRODUCTS.
•	IDENTIFY THE SPLITOFF POINT IN JOINT-COST SITUATION AND ALLOCATE JOINT COSTS USING VARIOUS METHODS (SALES VALUE AT SPLIT-OFF, PHYSICAL MEASURE, NET REALIZABLE VALUE (NRV), AND CONSTANT GROSS MARGIN NRV).
•	IDENTIFY AND CATEGORIZE COSTS OF QUALITY;
•	USE THE THEORY OF CONSTRAINTS AND THROUGHPUT ANALYSIS IN DECISION MAKING;
•	USE THE EOQ AND JIT MODELS OF INVENTORY MANAGEMENT;
EVALUATE INVESTMENT PROJECTS USING DISCOUNTED CASH FLOW AND OTHER TECHNIQUES
